The inferiorities of capacity ininfancy‚ minority, wardship, curatel, were not so considerable as those which we have hitherto examined. The duties of the guardian related both to the person and to the property of the ward. In respect of his person, the guardian was charged with the care of his nurture and education. in respect of his property, the guardian' s function was distinguished as either exclusive administration or concurrent interposition of authority.
